Leyds is one of four changes to the side that lost 34-27 in the dying minutes against the Waratahs in Sydney last week Saturday. JOHANNESBURG - Utility back Dillyn Leyds will start at flyhalf in place of the injured youngster Damian Willemse for the Stormers' match against the Crusaders in Christchurch. Leyds’ only other appearance in the number 10 jersey was the Stormers' win over the Blues at Newlands last year. He is one of four changes to the side that lost 34-27 in the dying minutes against the Waratahs in Sydney last week Saturday. Seabelo Senatla comes in for Leyds on the wing, while EW Viljeon comes in for the injured JJ Engelbrecht at outside center in the other change in the backline. In the front row, experienced loosehead prop JC Janse van Rensburg makes his first start of the season, with Steven Kitshoff set to make an impact from the replacements bench, while in the loose trio Cobus Wiese is back at blindside flank after missing out last week. Stormers – 15 SP Marais, 14 Seabelo Senatla, 13 EW Viljoen, 12 Damian de Allende, 11 Raymond Rhule, 10 Dillyn Leyds, 9 Dewaldt Duvenage, 8 Nizaam Carr, 7 Cobus Wiese, 6 Siya Kolisi (c), 5 Pieter-Steph du Toit, 4 JD Schickerling, 3 Wilco Louw, 2 Ramone Samuels, 1 JC Janse van Rensburg. Subs: 16 Dean Muir, 17 Steven Kitshoff, 18 Carlu Sadie, 19 Jan de Klerk, 20 Sikhumbuzo Notshe, 21 Kobus van Dyk, 22 Justin Phillips, 23 George Whitehead.